In Memphis and other areas up and down the Mississippi Valley people
are concerned about the prediction of an earthquake on 3 December
along the New Madrid fault. In some areas, thousands of people are
crowding into earthquake survival classes while entrepreneurs are
hawking quake insurance, and gas-line safety gadgets.

In Arkansas and Missouri, some schools and business have announced
plans to close in early December.

Everybody talks about the San Andreas Fault in California, but the
Midwest actually has had three of the most powerful earthquakes on
this continent.

In actuality, scientists say that there is no way to predict when an
earthquake will occur.</SUM>
